25 Nov 2016 Guinea: Guineans more trusting of doctors, hospitals since Ebola
http://www.voanews.com/a/guineans-more-trusting-of-doctors-hospitals-since-ebola/3611177.html
[Traditional healers who treat the ill are, after the Ebola virus disease (EVD) epidemic, more likely to use more western approaches (such as chlorine bleach) in their work. The healers are also more likely to refer their patients to medical care facilities as soon as signs of possible severe infectious diseases appear.]
Video:
http://av.voanews.com/Videoroot/Pangeavideo/2016/11/a/a4/a41adbcc-5b2f-43a9-b352-ff8992d300a0.mp4

23 Nov 2016: Rapid testing crucial during Ebola outbreaks
http://www.voanews.com/a/rapid-testing-crucial-during-ebola-outbreaks/3608168.html
TV program: http://www.voanews.com/programindex.html?tab=tv
Radio program: http://www.voanews.com/programindex.html?tab=Radio
[During the 2013 Ebola virus disease [EVD] outbreak, countries with already poor health care systems struggled to contain the early stages of the outbreak, and one of the worst problems they faced was the lack of any quick, reliable way to identify patients infected with the virus. According to Matt Scullion of BioFire Defense: "Tests would take 2 or 3, sometimes 4 days to get results back to hospitals. In the meantime, you had malaria patients in with Ebola patients, and if you didn't have Ebola before, you'd be likely to have Ebola after."
But as Ebola was multiplying unchecked across large areas of West Africa, a rapid-testing kit that had been in the works for years was ready to go at BioFire Defense, more than 10 000 km away in the western United States. The US firm, a subsidiary of a large French biomedical corporation, focuses on innovative technologies to help workers in the life sciences identify pathogens quickly and easily...
FilmArray is now one of 7 diagnostic tools the World Health Organization has approved for emergency use. According to the inspector general of Guinea's Health Ministry, Aboubakar Sidiki Diakite: "Before, we had to transport samples to Dakar, Senegal, or Lyon, France. But today, thanks to our partners in France, CDC in the US, and many others, we are able to make rapid diagnoses for EVD.]

[Rapid diagnosis is a key component of controlling spread of the virus, as infected individuals can be more quickly separated from individuals presenting with similar symptoms from other diseases. - Mod.LK]

Economy
-------
25 Nov 2016 Nigeria: firms in bid to secure Nigeria oil contracts
http://allafrica.com/view/group/main/main/id/00047511.html
About 224 companies, hundreds of them indigenous Nigerian firms, are seeking to secure contracts for the sale and purchase of Nigerian crude oil grades on offer in 2017. [Nigeria's economy is heavily dependent on income from oil sales. The country is the largest African crude oil supplier to India; it annually exports 400 000 barrels per day to India valued at USD 10 billion annually. India is the largest purchaser of Nigerian oil, which fulfills 20 per cent to 25 per cent of India's domestic oil demand.]

